1 olive oil
1 packet Beef Rump
½ tin chickpeas
1 flatbreads
1 cucumber
1 tomato
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 packet Mango Mayonnaise
1 packet Roasted Peanuts & Cashew Mix
1 bag coriander
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend

• Place beef between two sheets of
baking paper. Pound with rolling pin
until slightly flattened (this ensures it’s
extra tender!)
• In a bowl, combine beef, Mumbai spice
blend and a drizzle of olive oil
• Heat oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef for 5-6 mins or until cooked
to your liking
• Transfer to a plate to rest

• Drain chickpeas (1/2 tin for 2P/ 1 tin
for 4P)
• Wipe out pan, return to medium-high
heat with drizzle of oil. Add chickpeas
and Indian spice blend and toss until
warmed through, 2 mins. Transfer to a
bowl
• Return pan to medium-high heat.
Drizzle flatbreads with oil. Cook
flatbreads (1 for 2P / 2 for 4P) until
warmed through, 1-2 mins each side
• Roughly chop cucumber and tomato

• In a bowl, combine mixed salad leaves,
cucumber, tomato, dressing and a
drizzle of oil. Season
• Slice steak. Plate up salad, chickpeas
and steak
• Top with mayo, nuts and torn
coriander
• Serve with flatbreads